# If false, a Verilog instance with ports that do not match the Verilog 
	# module or library cell definition will cause an error and exit.  If true, 
	# an error message occurs, but the extra ports are added to the module 
	# or library cell definition to allow the inconsistent netlist to be read 
	# in and debugged further. The default value is false i.e. 'dirty netlists' 
	# are not tolerated.